The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Hyderabad, Jan. 7: Former Satyam Computers chairman B. Ramalinga Raju and five others were chargesheeted by the CBI today for allegedly filing false income tax returns resulting in a loss of Rs 126.57 crore to the company and shareholders. The others chargesheeted include his brother B. Rama Raju, the then CFO V. Srinivas, former Satyam vice-president (finance) G. Ramakrishna, and two Price Waterhouse auditors  S. Gopalakrishnan and Talluri Srinivas.                            
	 New York, Jan. 7: Resisting a hostile takeover bid by US-based Kraft Foods, British confectionery major Cadbury has held talks with American chocolate maker Hershey to encourage a rival offer, The Wall Street Journal said.                            
	 Shanghai, Jan. 7: Chinas central bank surprised markets today by raising the interest rate on its three-month bills for the first time since August.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 7: ICICI and Axis Bank have slashed their car loan rates for new customers. ICICI Bank has cut its rates by 0.25-0.5 per cent, while Axis Bank trimmed them by 0.5-0.75 per cent.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 7: Sebi today said a permanent account number (PAN) is mandatory for transfer of shares to an heir in case the deceased shareholder was the sole owner of the shares.
                                                                                                                          
